com.github.xemiru.luamesh

Class LuaMesh

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.xemiru.luamesh.LuaMesh

  • public class LuaMesh
extends java.lang.Object
    Primary class for LuaMesh.

    Public static variables within this class configure behaviors of name enforcement with Lua-coercible types, when translated into a Lua environment. These must be set before registration of any Lua-coercible classes.

    LuaMesh provides an extra function for receiving typenames of Java objects within Lua. See FunctionCType.

      • getLuaName

        public static java.lang.String getLuaName(java.lang.String name)
        Returns the Lua name of the given class name, in the format returned by Class.getName().

        If the given class has no associated name, this instead returns "<unknown type>".

        Parameters:
        name - the class name to get the name for
        Returns:
        the Lua name of the given class, or "nil" if passed null
